<paragraph id="E7407F437F5D54497D4AFA060A50C95C" blockId="1.[809,1452,1424,1607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497D4AFA060A52CABC" authority="Miranda Ribeiro, 1918: 106" authorityName="Miranda Ribeiro" authorityPageNumber="106" authorityYear="1918" box="[809,1289,1424,1447]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497D4AFA060C9FCABC" box="[809,964,1424,1447]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Pareiorhaphis</emphasis>
Miranda Ribeiro, 1918: 106
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="3844C1E17F5D54497B75FA060A10CABC" box="[1302,1355,1424,1447]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497D2CFA260B24CADC" baseAuthorityName="Steindachner" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[847,1151,1456,1479]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="calmoni">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497D2CFA260B24CADC" box="[847,1151,1456,1479]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Hemipsilichthys calmoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497ACBFA260B67CAFC" authority="Steindachner, 1907" authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1907" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Psilichthys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cameroni">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497ACBFA260AF0CADC" box="[1192,1451,1456,1479]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Psilichthys cameroni</emphasis>
Steindachner, 1907
</taxonomicName>
). 
<typeStatus id="3844C1E17F5D54497A35FA460BD4CAFC" box="[1110,1167,1488,1511]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Type</typeStatus>
species by subsequent designation by Regan (1920: 14). Gender: feminine. Subsequent 
<typeStatus id="3844C1E17F5D54497DB0F9860B5AC93C" box="[979,1025,1552,1575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">type</typeStatus>
species designation by 
<bibRefCitation id="836E02B27F5D54497B6AF9860CDBC95C" author="Gosline, W" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" pagination="79 - 134" refId="ref5129" refString="Gosline, W. A. 1947. Contributions to the classification of the loricariid catfishes. Arquivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro, 41: 79 - 134." type="journal article" year="1947">Gosline (1947: 102)</bibRefCitation>
of 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497DC1F9A60BC0C95C" authorityName="Miranda Ribeiro" authorityYear="1907" box="[930,1179,1584,1607]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duseni">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497DC1F9A60BC0C95C" box="[930,1179,1584,1607]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Hemipsilichthys duseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is invalid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AFE52CC87F5D544A7D4AF9E60DF5CCB2" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="445" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E7407F437F5D544A7D4AF9E60DB8CEB2" blockId="1.[809,1452,1648,1959]" lastBlockId="2.[136,779,178,937]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="445" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497D4AF9E60CC3C99C" bold="true" box="[809,920,1648,1671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497DC7F9E60B1BC99C" authorityName="Miranda Ribeiro" authorityYear="1918" box="[932,1088,1648,1671]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497DC7F9E60B1BC99C" box="[932,1088,1648,1671]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Pareiorhaphis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is diagnosed among loricariids by having the following synapomorphies. (1) Cheeks (postrostral and cheek plates) covered with hypertrophied odontodes in nuptial males. This character is shared with delturines, 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497D4AF9660B03C81C" baseAuthorityName="Miranda Ribeiro" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[809,1112,1776,1799]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="duseni">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497D4AF9660B03C81C" box="[809,1112,1776,1799]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Isbrueckerichthys duseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and some loricariines and hypostomines. (2) Opercle with hypertrophied odontodes in nuptial males. Present in all 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497A3EF8A60BA2C85C" authorityName="Miranda Ribeiro" authorityYear="1918" box="[1117,1273,1840,1863]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497A3EF8A60BA2C85C" box="[1117,1273,1840,1863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Pareiorhaphis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shared with 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497D4AF8C60C8CC87C" authorityName="Eigenmann &amp; Eigenmann" authorityYear="1889" box="[809,983,1872,1895]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497D4AF8C60C8CC87C" box="[809,983,1872,1895]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Hemipsilichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and some loricariines. (3) Exposed lateral process of cleithum with hypertrophied odontodes in nuptial males. Present in all 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5D54497A6AF8060BA1C8BC" box="[1033,1274,1936,1959]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="444" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5D54497A6AF8060BFEC8BC" box="[1033,1189,1936,1959]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="444">Pareiorhaphis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
and shared with 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7EEBFF240EC4CFD2" baseAuthorityName="Lutken" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[136,415,178,201]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gobio">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7EEBFF240EC4CFD2" box="[136,415,178,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">Hemipsilichthys gobio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7F87FF240DD3CFD2" authorityName="Pereira, Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa" authorityYear="2000" box="[484,648,178,201]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="papillatus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7F87FF240DD3CFD2" box="[484,648,178,201]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">H. papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and some loricariines. (4) Lateroventral portion of preopercle deeply rugose due to the implantation of hypertrophied odontodes in nuptial males. Present in all 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7F84FE840D81CE32" box="[487,730,274,297]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7F84FE840DD8CE32" box="[487,643,274,297]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">Pareiorhaphis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
and shared with 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7F64FEA40E3ACE52" baseAuthorityName="Lutken" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[263,353,306,329]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gobio">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7F64FEA40E3ACE52" box="[263,353,306,329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">H. gobio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7FF1FEA40D40CE52" authorityName="Pereira, Oliveira &amp; Oyakawa" authorityYear="2000" box="[402,539,306,329]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemipsilichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="papillatus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7FF1FEA40D40CE52" box="[402,539,306,329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">H. papillatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The characters shared with the groups above are most parsimoniously interpreted as independently derived according to the discussion of relationships in 
<bibRefCitation id="836E02B27F5E544A7F4DFE040EAECEB2" author="Armbruster, J" box="[302,501,402,425]" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref5089" refString="Armbruster, J. W. 2004. Phylogenetic relationships of the suckermouth armoured catfishes (Loricariidae) with emphasis on the Hypostominae and the Ancistrinae. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 141: 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="2004">Armbruster (2004)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="836E02B27F5E544A7C44FE040D84CEB2" author="Reis, R" box="[551,735,402,425]" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" pagination="277 - 299" refId="ref5394" refString="Reis, R. E., E. H. L. Pereira &amp; J. W. Armbruster. 2006. Delturinae, a new loricariid catfish subfamily (Teleostei, Siluriformes), with a revision of Delturus and Hemipsilichthys. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 147: 277 - 299." type="journal article" year="2006">
Reis 
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7C38FE040DD2CEB2" box="[603,649,402,425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">et al</emphasis>
. (2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7407F437F5E544A7ECDFE240DF5CCB2" blockId="2.[136,779,178,937]" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">
The following characters are also useful to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7EEBFE440E28CEF2" box="[136,371,466,489]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhaphis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7EEBFE440E7ACEF2" box="[136,289,466,489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">Pareiorhaphis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
from the remaining neoplecostomines. Abdomen naked or with small embedded platelets and lower lip without a series of distinct papillae behind the dentaries (
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7EF2FDA40FFCCD52" box="[145,167,562,585]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">vs</emphasis>
abdomen with plates forming a central polygonal path and lower lip with a series of distinct papillae behind the dentaries in 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7F70FDE40E9FCD92" authorityName="C.H.Eigenmann &amp; R.S.Eigenmann" authorityYear="1888" box="[275,452,626,649]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Neoplecostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7F70FDE40E9FCD92" box="[275,452,626,649]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">Neoplecostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); infraorbital series of plates forming the lateral edge on the nasal opening and dorsal-fin spinelet usually present (
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7FF8FD240EEACDD2" box="[411,433,690,713]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">vs</emphasis>
infraorbital series of plates not forming the lateral edge of the nasal opening and dorsal-fin spinelet absent in 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7F34FD640D42CC12" authorityName="Derijst" authorityYear="1996" box="[343,537,754,777]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Isbrueckerichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7F34FD640D42CC12" box="[343,537,754,777]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">Isbrueckerichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); adipose fin present (
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7EF2FC840FFCCC32" box="[145,167,786,809]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">vs</emphasis>
absent in 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7F71FC840ECDCC32" authorityName="Gosline" authorityYear="1947" box="[274,406,786,809]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Pareiorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7F71FC840ECDCC32" box="[274,406,786,809]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">Pareiorhina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); tooth series in dentary straight or slightly curved and odontodes on ventral surface of pelvicfin spine aligned with the spine axis (
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7C6AFCC40D44CC72" box="[521,543,850,873]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">vs</emphasis>
tooth series in dentary approximately U-shaped and odontodes on ventral surface of pelvic-fin spine turned medially in 
<taxonomicName id="20FF04C07F5E544A7C79FC040DC5CCB2" box="[538,670,914,937]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Kronichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="445" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D58BA3517F5E544A7C79FC040DC5CCB2" box="[538,670,914,937]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="445">Kronichthys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
